23class Traverser : public TIntermTraverser
24{
25 public:
26 ANGLE_NO_DISCARD static bool Apply(TCompiler *compiler,
27 TIntermNode *root,
28 const TSymbolTable &symbolTable,
29 TIntermBinary *flipXY,
30 TIntermTyped *fragRotation,
31 int ShaderVersion);
32
33 private:
34 Traverser(TIntermBinary *flipXY,
35 TIntermTyped *fragRotation,
36 TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
37 int shaderVersion);
38 bool visitAggregate(Visit visit, TIntermAggregate *node) override;
39
40 TIntermBinary *mFlipXY = nullptr;
41 TIntermTyped *mFragRotation = nullptr;
42 const TSymbolTable *symbolTable = nullptr;
43 const int shaderVersion;
44};
45
46Traverser::Traverser(TIntermBinary *flipXY,
47 TIntermTyped *fragRotation,
48 TSymbolTable *symbolTable,
49 int shaderVersion)
50 : TIntermTraverser(true, false, false, symbolTable),
51 mFlipXY(flipXY),
52 mFragRotation(fragRotation),
53 symbolTable(symbolTable),
54 shaderVersion(shaderVersion)
55{}
56
57// static
58bool Traverser::Apply(TCompiler *compiler,
59 TIntermNode *root,
60 const TSymbolTable &symbolTable,
61 TIntermBinary *flipXY,
62 TIntermTyped *fragRotation,
63 int shaderVersion)
64{
65 TSymbolTable *pSymbolTable = const_cast<TSymbolTable *>(&symbolTable);
66 Traverser traverser(flipXY, fragRotation, pSymbolTable, shaderVersion);
67 root->traverse(&traverser);
68 return traverser.updateTree(compiler, root);
69}
70
71bool Traverser::visitAggregate(Visit visit, TIntermAggregate *node)
72{
73 // Decide if the node represents the call of texelFetchOffset.
74 if (node->getOp() != EOpCallBuiltInFunction)
75 {
76 return true;
77 }
78
79 ASSERT(node->getFunction()->symbolType() == SymbolType::BuiltIn);
80 if (node->getFunction()->name() != "interpolateAtOffset")
81 {
82 return true;
83 }
84
85 const TIntermSequence *sequence = node->getSequence();
86 ASSERT(sequence->size() == 2u);
87
88 TIntermSequence *interpolateAtOffsetArguments = new TIntermSequence();
89 // interpolant node
90 interpolateAtOffsetArguments->push_back(sequence->at(0));
91 // offset
92 TIntermTyped *offsetNode = sequence->at(1)->getAsTyped();
93 ASSERT(offsetNode->getType() == *(StaticType::GetBasic<EbtFloat, 2>()));
94
95 // If pre-rotation is enabled apply the transformation else just flip the Y-coordinate
96 TIntermTyped *rotatedXY;
97 if (mFragRotation)
98 {
99 rotatedXY =
100 new TIntermBinary(EOpMatrixTimesVector, mFragRotation->deepCopy(), mFlipXY->deepCopy());
101 }
102 else
103 {
104 rotatedXY = mFlipXY->deepCopy();
105 }
106
107 TIntermBinary *correctedOffset = new TIntermBinary(EOpMul, offsetNode, rotatedXY);
108 correctedOffset->setLine(offsetNode->getLine());
109 interpolateAtOffsetArguments->push_back(correctedOffset);
110
111 TIntermTyped *interpolateAtOffsetNode = CreateBuiltInFunctionCallNode(
112 "interpolateAtOffset", interpolateAtOffsetArguments, *symbolTable, shaderVersion);
113 interpolateAtOffsetNode->setLine(node->getLine());
114
115 // Replace the old node by this new node.
116 queueReplacement(interpolateAtOffsetNode, OriginalNode::IS_DROPPED);
117
118 return true;
119}
120
121} // anonymous namespace
122
123bool RewriteInterpolateAtOffset(TCompiler *compiler,
124 TIntermNode *root,
125 const TSymbolTable &symbolTable,
126 int shaderVersion,
127 TIntermBinary *flipXY,
128 TIntermTyped *fragRotation)
129{
130 // interpolateAtOffset is only valid in GLSL 3.0 and later.
131 if (shaderVersion < 300)
132 {
133 return true;
134 }
135
136 return Traverser::Apply(compiler, root, symbolTable, flipXY, fragRotation, shaderVersion);
137}
